@page "/"
@page "/init"

<div class="home-product-page">
    <section class="init-product-hero" style="background-image: url('@AssetPaths.Init.Hero');">
        <div class="init-product-hero__overlay"></div>
        <div class="init-product-hero__content">
            <p class="jpv-kicker">init / JPV-OS Access Gateway</p>
            <h1>Welcome to the Venture.</h1>
            <p class="init-product-hero__lead">
                Connected digital infrastructure for creators, operators, partners, and enterprise systems unified through the JPV ecosystem.
            </p>
            <div class="init-product-hero__actions">
                <a class="jpv-button jpv-button-primary" href="/pricing">Get init</a>
                <a class="jpv-button jpv-button-secondary" href="/pricing">Explore Access</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section product-section">
        <SectionHeader Kicker="What init does"
                       Title="What init helps you do."
                       Description="A cleaner entry point for access, packages, partners, creators, and operational workflows." />

        <div class="product-value-grid">
            <article class="product-value-card">
                <span>01</span>
                <h2>Access routing</h2>
                <p>Move members, creators, partners, and enterprise requests into the right pathway without scattered links or manual handoffs.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="product-value-card">
                <span>02</span>
                <h2>Package activation</h2>
                <p>Connect paid packages, access levels, resource delivery, and onboarding into a cleaner launch flow.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="product-value-card">
                <span>03</span>
                <h2>Partner coordination</h2>
                <p>Route platform, cloud, AI, creative, and infrastructure relationships through one operational surface.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="product-value-card">
                <span>04</span>
                <h2>Governance alignment</h2>
                <p>Keep public-facing access, internal review, and implementation decisions tied to JPV-OS standards.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section product-split-section">
        <div class="product-split-copy">
            <p class="jpv-kicker">Why it is different</p>
            <h2>Built for structured execution, not scattered tools.</h2>
            <p>
                Most creator and partner systems are split across link pages, checkout tools, forms, chats, spreadsheets, and disconnected dashboards.
                init brings those entry points into one branded access layer so people know where to go, what they get, and how the ecosystem moves.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="product-proof-grid">
            <div>Unified access instead of scattered links.</div>
            <div>Packages tied to actual outcomes.</div>
            <div>Partner routing with implementation context.</div>
            <div>Creator-facing growth connected to infrastructure standards.</div>
            <div>Governance and operations visible before scale.</div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section product-section">
        <SectionHeader Kicker="Access paths"
                       Title="Choose the right path."
                       Description="Each route is designed around what someone needs to do next, not just what label they fit into." />

        <div class="access-grid product-access-grid">
            <RouteTile Eyebrow="Member"
                       Title="Member Access"
                       Description="For people who want updates, resources, and structured ecosystem entry."
                       Href="/pricing" />

            <RouteTile Eyebrow="Creator"
                       Title="Creator Launch"
                       Description="For creators and builders who need launch support, resource packaging, community access, and venture-facing pathways."
                       Href="/pricing" />

            <RouteTile Eyebrow="Partner"
                       Title="Partner Package"
                       Description="For collaborators, platforms, and service partners who need infrastructure alignment, visibility, and implementation routing."
                       Href="/pricing" />

            <RouteTile Eyebrow="Enterprise"
                       Title="Enterprise Infrastructure"
                       Description="For larger implementation needs requiring private review, infrastructure planning, and operational alignment."
                       Href="/pricing" />

            <RouteTile Eyebrow="Custom"
                       Title="Custom Implementation"
                       Description="For scoped buildouts, access systems, deployment support, and tailored workflows."
                       Href="/contact" />
        </div>
    </section>
</div>


<section id="founder" class="jpv-section jpv-founder-section">
    <div class="jpv-section-grid founder-grid">

        <div class="founder-visual glass-panel">
            <div class="founder-orb"></div>

            <div class="founder-frame">
                <img
    src="/assets/founder/jay-price-founder.png"
    alt="Jay Price, founder of the JPV ecosystem"
    class="founder-image"
/>
            </div>

            <div class="founder-meta">
                <span>Founder Architecture</span>
                <strong>Jay Price</strong>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="founder-copy">
            <span class="section-kicker">
                ABOUT THE FOUNDER
            </span>

            <h2>
                Building connected digital infrastructure.
            </h2>

            <p>
                Jay Price founded the JPV ecosystem to unify modern
                digital operations across infrastructure,
                creator systems, research initiatives,
                and enterprise execution.
            </p>

            <p>
                The ecosystem combines operational architecture,
                access systems, automation, governance standards,
                and scalable platform coordination into a connected
                environment designed for long-term adaptability.
            </p>

            <div class="capability-grid">
                <span>JPV-OS</span>
                <span>Access Gateway</span>
                <span>Creator Infrastructure</span>
                <span>Enterprise Systems</span>
                <span>Research & Governance</span>
                <span>AI Operations</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<section id="how-it-works" class="jpv-section">

    <span class="section-kicker">
        HOW IT WORKS
    </span>

    <h2 class="section-title">
        Access moves through a governed flow.
    </h2>

    <div class="process-grid">

        <div class="process-card glass-panel">
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Choose Access</h3>
            <p>
                Select the tier that matches member,
                creator, operator, enterprise,
                or sovereign needs.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="process-card glass-panel">
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Stripe Checkout</h3>
            <p>
                Payments route through Stripe for subscriptions,
                annual access, upgrades,
                and enterprise billing.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="process-card glass-panel">
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Discord Routing</h3>
            <p>
                Member and VIP Venture access connects
                to Discord-based ecosystem channels.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="process-card glass-panel">
            <span>04</span>
            <h3>Ecosystem Unlock</h3>
            <p>
                Access expands across platform areas,
                creator systems,
                operational resources,
                and support paths.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>

<section id="access" class="jpv-section">

    <span class="section-kicker">
        ACCESS PACKAGES
    </span>

    <h2 class="section-title">
        Structured access without random pricing.
    </h2>

    <div class="pricing-grid">

        <div class="price-card glass-panel">
            <h3>Member</h3>
            <strong>$10/mo</strong>
            <p>
                Community access,
                core updates,
                and member routing.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="price-card glass-panel">
            <h3>VIP Venture</h3>
            <strong>$30/mo</strong>
            <p>
                Priority Discord access,
                venture visibility,
                and expanded ecosystem channels.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="price-card glass-panel">
            <h3>Creator Lane</h3>
            <strong>$80/mo</strong>
            <p>
                Creator systems,
                launch resources,
                and ecosystem positioning.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="price-card glass-panel">
            <h3>Operator</h3>
            <strong>$250/mo</strong>
            <p>
                Operational workflows,
                implementation visibility,
                and advanced support paths.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="price-card glass-panel">
            <h3>Enterprise</h3>
            <strong>$900/mo</strong>
            <p>
                Enterprise packages,
                infrastructure coordination,
                and partner execution support.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="price-card glass-panel">
            <h3>Sovereign</h3>
            <strong>Custom</strong>
            <p>
                Custom ecosystem architecture,
                governance alignment,
                and strategic deployment planning.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>

<section id="faq" class="jpv-section">

    <span class="section-kicker">
        FAQ
    </span>

    <h2 class="section-title">
        Clear answers before access begins.
    </h2>

    <div class="faq-grid">

        <details class="glass-panel" open>
            <summary>
                How are payments handled?
            </summary>

            <p>
                All paid access routes through Stripe for subscriptions,
                billing, upgrades,
                and ecosystem provisioning.
            </p>
        </details>

        <details class="glass-panel">
            <summary>
                Is Discord required?
            </summary>

            <p>
                Member and VIP Venture access connect
                to Discord-based ecosystem channels.
            </p>
        </details>

        <details class="glass-panel">
            <summary>
                Can tiers be upgraded?
            </summary>

            <p>
                Yes.
                Access can scale from member access
                into creator, operator,
                enterprise, or sovereign routing.
            </p>
        </details>

        <details class="glass-panel">
            <summary>
                Are enterprise plans custom?
            </summary>

            <p>
                Enterprise and Sovereign access include
                direct intake, alignment,
                and implementation review.
            </p>
        </details>

    </div>
</section>

<section id="final-cta" class="jpv-section final-cta glass-panel">

    <span class="section-kicker">
        READY FOR ACCESS
    </span>

    <h2>
        Welcome to the Venture.
    </h2>

    <p>
        Choose access,
        route through Stripe,
        unlock the correct ecosystem layer,
        and move with operational clarity.
    </p>

    <div class="cta-actions">

        <a href="/pricing" class="jpv-button primary">
            View Access Packages
        </a>

        <a href="/contact" class="jpv-button secondary">
            Contact the Team
        </a>

    </div>
</section>




